"Operation instructions: 1. The steps to activate an MBN: Step 1: Select the slot of MBN to be activated, which is usually loaded by double cards, and the default is double cards. Step 2: You need to select a name of the MBN to be activated. The commonly used MBN is prefabricated in the drop-down list. If it is not found, you can enter the keyword of the MBN name to be activated in the search box to find the MBN you need to activate. Step 3: Click the Activate button to load the selected MBN. 2. Recovery system default MBN can be achieved by clicking the Restore default MBN button. 3. It can display the information of MBN loaded in the current Modem. The first line shows whether the MBN loaded by the current Modem is the default MBN of the system. (Some products may not be integrated into the relevant interface, this line will show: Not Supported) The second line shows the name and version number of Default MBN and Carrier MBN currently loaded in Modem. Our custom loaded MBN is Carrier MBN, SUB0 is card 1, SUB1 is card 2."
